b>, <b>14g of protein<\\/b>, and <b>9g of fat<\\/b>. For <b>88 cents per serving<\\/b>, this recipe <b>covers 9%<\\/b> of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. It is a good option if you\'re following a <b>dairy free<\\/b> diet. A few people really liked this breakfast. This recipe from Foodista has 98 fans. A mixture of knorr hollandaise sauce, canadian bacon, eggs, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so yummy. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about <b>about 45 minutes<\\/b>. With a spoonacular <b>score of 37%<\\/b>, this dish is not so excellent. Similar recipes include <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipes\\/classic-eggs-benedict-163878\\\">Classic Eggs Benedict<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipes\\/classic-eggs-benedict-78160\\\">Classic Eggs Benedict<\\/a>, and <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipes\\/classic-eggs-benedict-21114\\\">Classic Eggs Benedict<\\/a>.\",\"cuisines\":[\"American\"],\"dishTypes\":[\"morning meal\",\"brunch\",\"breakfast\"],\"diets\":[\"dairy free\"],\"occasions\":[],\"winePairing\":{\"pairedWines\":[\"chardonnay\",\"cava\"],\"pairingText\":\"Eggs Benedict can be paired with Chardonnay and Cava. Sparkling wine--with our without orange juice--is an obvious choice for eggs. With buttery hollandaise sauce, though, you might opt for a fuller white wine like chardonnay. The Cupcake Vineyards Butterkissed Chardonnay with a 4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 11 dollars per bottle.\",\"productMatches\":[{\"id\":473408,\"title\":\"Cupcake Vineyards Butterkissed Chardonnay\",\"description\":\"Butterkissed Chardonnay is a rich, decadenttake on a timeless varietal. We grow our grapes inthe sun-drenched vineyards of California, wherethe long, warm growing season helps us coaxrich, indulgent flavors into the bottle. Stainlesssteel and barrel fermentation lead to fresharomas of ripe pear and white peach. 100% ofthe wine goes through malolactic fermentation,resulting in a rich Chardonnay with notes offreshly drawn butter, vanilla and citrus zest witha smooth, creamy mouthfeel.This decadent, full-bodied wine pairs well withimpromptu get-togethers with friends, woodfired pizza or parmesan crusted chicken breast.\",\"price\":\"$10.99\",\"imageUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/productImages\\/473408-312x231.jpg\",\"averageRating\":0.8,\"ratingCount\":30,\"score\":0.7890109890109891,\"link\":\"https:\\/\\/click.linksynergy.com\\/deeplink?id=*QCiIS6t4gA&mid=2025&murl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wine.com%2Fproduct%2Fcupcake-vineyards-butterkissed-chardonnay-2017%2F509991\"}]},\"instructions\":\"Prepare Knorr Hollandaise Sauce according to package instructions.\\nBrown Canadian Bacon in a frying pan and toast English muffins. While bacon is cooking, poach the eggs.\\nFill a medium sized sauce pan half way with water. Add 1\\/2 teaspoon of white vinegar (this is optional but the vinegar helps hold the egg together). Bring to a gentle boil and carefully add eggs (1-2 at a time works best). Poach eggs for 2-3 minutes or until yolk has set to your preference. Remove eggs one at a time with a slotted spoon.\\nLayer ingredients as follows: English muffin, Canadian Bacon, Eggs, Hollandaise Sauce.\",\"analyzedInstructions\":[{\"name\":\"\",\"steps\":[{\"number\":1,\"step\":\"Prepare Knorr Hollandaise Sauce according to package instructions.\",\"ingredients\":[{\"id\":93801,\"name\":\"hollandaise sauce\",\"localizedName\":\"hollandaise sauce\",\"image\":\"hollandaise-sauce.jpg\"}],\"equipment\":[]},{\"number\":2,\"step\":\"Brown Canadian Bacon in a frying pan and toast English muffins. While bacon is cooking, poach the eggs.\",\"ingredients\":[{\"id\":18439,\"name\":\"english muffin\",\"localizedName\":\"english muffin\",\"image\":\"English-muffins.jpg\"},{\"id\":10130,\"name\":\"canadian bacon\",\"localizedName\":\"canadian bacon\",\"image\":\"canadian-bacon.png\"},{\"id\":10123,\"name\":\"bacon\",\"lo