\",\"originalString\":\"2 Tb. Dijon mustard\",\"originalName\":\"Dijon mustard\",\"amount\":2,\"unit\":\"Tb\",\"meta\":[],\"metaInformation\":[],\"measures\":{\"us\":{\"amount\":2,\"unitShort\":\"Tb\",\"unitLong\":\"Tbs\"},\"metric\":{\"amount\":2,\"unitShort\":\"Tb\",\"unitLong\":\"Tbs\"}}},{\"id\":2028,\"aisle\":\"Spices and Seasonings\",\"image\":\"paprika.jpg\",\"consistency\":\"solid\",\"name\":\"paprika\",\"nameClean\":\"paprika\",\"original\":\"2 teaspoons paprika\",\"originalString\":\"2 teaspoons paprika\",\"originalName\":\"paprika\",\"amount\":2,\"unit\":\"teaspoons\",\"meta\":[],\"metaInformation\":[],\"measures\":{\"us\":{\"amount\":2,\"unitShort\":\"tsps\",\"unitLong\":\"teaspoons\"},\"metric\":{\"amount\":2,\"unitShort\":\"tsps\",\"unitLong\":\"teaspoons\"}}}],\"id\":639893,\"title\":\"Coffee-Infused Bbq Baby Back Ribs\",\"readyInMinutes\":45,\"servings\":6,\"sourceUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.foodista.com\\/recipe\\/FMGR8DZS\\/coffee-infused-bbq-baby-back-ribs\",\"image\":\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipeImages\\/639893-556x370.jpg\",\"imageType\":\"jpg\",\"summary\":\"The recipe Coffee-Infused Bbq Baby Back Ribs can be made <b>in approximately approximately 45 minutes<\\/b>. This recipe serves 6. One portion of this dish contains roughly <b>41g of protein<\\/b>, <b>34g of fat<\\/b>, and a total of <b>704 calories<\\/b>. For <b>$2.49 per serving<\\/b>, this recipe <b>covers 35%<\\/b> of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 27 people have tried and liked this recipe. It is a good option if you\'re following a <b>gluten free and dairy free<\\/b> diet. Head to the store and pick up garlic powder, cider vinegar, liquid smoke, and a few other things to make it today. It is brought to you by Foodista. A couple people really liked this main course. All things considered, we decided this recipe <b>deserves a spoonacular score of 79%<\\/b>. This score is solid. <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipes\\/keawe-grilled-baby-back-ribs-with-kona-coffee-bbq-grilling-and-dipping-sauce-746630\\\">Keawe Grilled Baby Back Ribs with Kona Coffee Bbq Grilling and Dipping Sauce<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipes\\/bbq-baby-back-ribs-268384\\\">BBQ Baby Back Ribs<\\/a>, and <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipes\\/beasty-bbq-baby-back-ribs-473377\\\">Beasty BBQ Baby Back Ribs<\\/a> are very similar to this recipe.\",\"cuisines\":[],\"dishTypes\":[\"lunch\",\"main course\",\"main dish\",\"dinner\"],\"diets\":[\"gluten free\",\"dairy free\"],\"occasions\":[],\"winePairing\":{\"pairedWines\":[\"pinot noir\",\"shiraz\",\"zinfandel\"],\"pairingText\":\"Pinot Noir, Shiraz, and Zinfandel are great choices for Baby Back Ribs. Pork ribs and other barbecued porks with sweet-and-spicy sauces work well with these red wines. You could try Carneros Hills Winery Pinot Noir. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.1 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 27 dollars per bottle.\",\"productMatches\":[{\"id\":438100,\"title\":\"Carneros Hills Winery Pinot Noir\",\"description\":\"The Carneros Hills Winery Pinot Noir exhibits aromas of sandalwood, wisteria, cinnamon, and forest floor that weave through bright cherry and raspberry fruit notes. On the palate, red currant, allspice, bacon and wild fennel arise, while a focused core of acidity and broadening minerality expand into fine-textured, mouth-coating tannins.\",\"price\":\"$26.99\",\"imageUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/productImages\\/438100-312x231.jpg\",\"averageRating\":0.82,\"ratingCount\":13,\"score\":0.7949999999999999,\"link\":\"https:\\/\\/click.linksynergy.com\\/deeplink?id=*QCiIS6t4gA&mid=2025&murl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wine.com%2Fproduct%2Fcarneros-hills-winery-pinot-noir-2014%2F173256\"}]},\"instructions\":\"Preheat the oven to *350. Mix the first seven ingredients in a small bowl.\\nCut each rack in several pieces and rub the spices over all the rib sections. You can leave the ribs whole if you like the way they look better--I just 