easpoon\"},\"metric\":{\"amount\":1,\"unitShort\":\"tsp\",\"unitLong\":\"teaspoon\"}}},{\"id\":19364,\"aisle\":\"Nut butters, Jams, and Honey;Frozen;Baking\",\"image\":\"caramel-sauce.jpg\",\"consistency\":\"solid\",\"name\":\"caramel sauce\",\"nameClean\":\"caramel sauce\",\"original\":\"Caramel Sauce, for drizzling\",\"originalString\":\"Caramel Sauce, for drizzling\",\"originalName\":\"Caramel Sauce, for drizzling\",\"amount\":21,\"unit\":\"servings\",\"meta\":[\"for drizzling\"],\"metaInformation\":[\"for drizzling\"],\"measures\":{\"us\":{\"amount\":21,\"unitShort\":\"servings\",\"unitLong\":\"servings\"},\"metric\":{\"amount\":21,\"unitShort\":\"servings\",\"unitLong\":\"servings\"}}}],\"id\":1095963,\"title\":\"MINI OATMEAL COOKIE CHEESECAKES\",\"readyInMinutes\":140,\"servings\":21,\"sourceUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.foodista.com\\/recipe\\/CY5KJZ7W\\/mini-oatmeal-cookie-cheesecakes-recipe\",\"image\":\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipeImages\\/1095963-556x370.jpeg\",\"imageType\":\"jpeg\",\"summary\":\"The recipe MINI OATMEAL COOKIE CHEESECAKES can be made <b>in around 2 hours and 20 minutes<\\/b>. For <b>86 cents per serving<\\/b>, this recipe <b>covers 7%<\\/b> of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. One serving contains <b>475 calories<\\/b>, <b>6g of protein<\\/b>, and <b>23g of fat<\\/b>. This recipe serves 21. This recipe from Foodista has 1 fans. It is a good option if you\'re following a <b>lacto ovo vegetarian<\\/b> diet. Only a few people really liked this dessert. If you have raisin, lemon juice, ground cinnamon, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. With a spoonacular <b>score of 15%<\\/b>, this dish is rather bad. Users who liked this recipe also liked <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipes\\/mini-lemon-cheesecakes-with-ginger-cookie-crust-699339\\\">Mini Lemon Cheesecakes with Ginger Cookie Crust<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipes\\/chocolate-chip-cookie-dough-mini-cheesecakes-61858\\\">Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Mini Cheesecakes<\\/a>, and <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/recipes\\/peanut-butter-mini-cheesecakes-with-chocolate-cookie-crust-538219\\\">Peanut Butter Mini Cheesecakes with Chocolate Cookie Crust<\\/a>.\",\"cuisines\":[],\"dishTypes\":[\"dessert\"],\"diets\":[\"lacto ovo vegetarian\"],\"occasions\":[],\"winePairing\":{\"pairedWines\":[\"lambrusco dolce\",\"late harvest riesling\",\"sauternes\"],\"pairingText\":\"Cheesecake can be paired with Lambrusco Dolce, Late Harvest Riesling, and Sauternes. White dessert wines are a safe pick for cheesecake (without chocolate), but a sweet lambrusco will be so good with classic strawberry cheesecake. You could try Chateau Chantal Late Harvest Riesling. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.5 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 21 dollars per bottle.\",\"productMatches\":[{\"id\":430249,\"title\":\"Chateau Chantal Late Harvest Riesling\",\"description\":null,\"price\":\"$21.0\",\"imageUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/spoonacular.com\\/productImages\\/430249-312x231.jpg\",\"averageRating\":0.9,\"ratingCount\":3,\"score\":0.8,\"link\":\"https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/Chateau-Chantal-Late-Harvest-Riesling\\/dp\\/B00IJI3V3I?tag=spoonacular-20\"}]},\"instructions\":\"<ol><li>For the oatmeal cookies, preheat oven to 350F. <\\/li><li>Using an electric mixer, cream together butter, brown sugar and sugar on medium speed, until light and fluffy. <\\/li><li>Beat in egg and vanilla extract until well combined. <\\/li><li>On low speed, add oats, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and raisins, mixing just until flour disappears. <\\/li><li>Place small spoonfuls of dough on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Bake for 6-8 minutes, until the edges are just golden. <\\/li><li>Remove from oven and let cool until ready to assemble.<\\/li><li>For the oatmeal cookie crust, preheat oven to 350F. <\\/li><li>Line muffin tins with 21 cupcake liners and lightly coat with non-stick cooking spray. <\\/li><li>In a small bowl, combine oats, flour, butter, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon, mixing until well combined. <\\/li><li>Press a heaping tablespoon in the bottoms of each cupcake liner and bake in preheated oven for 8 minutes. <\\/li><li>Remove from oven and let cool.<\\/li><li>For the cheesecake filling, lower oven temperature to 325F. <\\/li><li>Using an electric mixer, combine cream cheese and sugar. <\\/li><li>Beat at medium speed until well combined. <\\/li><li>Add eggs on low speed, one at a time, beating well after each addition. <\\/li><li>Add cream, flour, lemon juice and vanilla mixing until smooth and creamy. <\\/li><li>Fill each cup with the cheesecake mixture. <\\/li><li>Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 275F and continue to bake 15 minutes more. <\\/li><li>Remove from the oven and allow cupcakes to cool completely. <\\/li><li>Refrigerate for at least an hour before serving. <\\/li><li>To garnish, place a mini oatmeal cookie on top and drizzle caramel sauce over top of both.<\\/li><\\/ol>\",\"analyzedInstructions\":[{\"name\":\"\",\"steps\":[{\"number\":1,\"step\":\"For the oatmeal cookies, preheat oven to 350F. Using an electric mixer, cream together butter, brown sugar and sugar on medium speed, until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla extract until well combined. On low speed, add oats, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and raisins, mixing just until flour disappears.\",\"ingredients\":[{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"oatmeal cookie\",\"localizedName\":\"oatmeal cookie\",\"image\":\"shortbread-cookies.jpg\"},{\"id\":2050,\"name\":\"vanilla extract\",\"localizedName\":\"vanilla extract\",\"image\":\"vanilla-extract.jpg\"},{\"id\":18372,\"name\":\"baking soda\",\"localizedName\":\"baking soda\",\"image\":\"white-powder.jpg\"},{\"id\":19334,\"name\":\"brown sugar\",\"localizedName\":\"brown sugar\",\"image\":\"dark-brown-sugar.png\"},{\"id\":2010,\"name\":\"cinnamon\",\"localizedName\":\"cinnamon\",\"image\":\"cinnamon.jpg\"},{\"id\":9299,\"name\":\"raisins\",\